name: Pharaoh's Dance
comments: Bitches Brew will always make me feel high! Forever.

@JBT iTunes actually has most of their mp3's at like 128 I believe, even better. also I feel I'm finally starting to sort of understand this album, at least to the point where I enjoy it but don't fully comprehend it

I just love this phase of Miles Davis's work.
I think his previous album (In a Silent Way) is even better then Bitches Brew!
Glass of wine, spacy tobacco, and here we go... The start of an epic voyage :)
No dude, let him buy it on itunes, everyone knows jazz sounds amazing at 256kbps
This is amazing, I'm buying this track right now
I don't think you can call it 'real jazz' coz of the way how it was recorded and produced. This thing is beyond any 'labels'.
Opens the deepest secluded corners of my soul...
Miles' playing in Pharaoh's Dance.. leading the way
